text: I hate the word should don't all
over yourself often times when we say
the word should it's somebody else's
should so we're thinking of what our
parents would think or what our friends
or community would think but in fact
when we've quiet those should voices we
can really listen to what we want and
when we use the word should we usually
say it in a slightly apologetic tone so
I should do this but I really want to do
that and I'm trying to encourage people
to replace the word
should with the word want replacing the
word should with the word what makes us
more authentic and happier because we
realized that we're living the life that
we want to live where we're not
following someone else's formula
who's telling us what will make us happy
we're actually listening to our gut our
instinct our heart and that's always a
good thing I think we overthink dating
and love and I only really have one rule
for you which is to get in here listen
to your instinct and not other people's
ideas of what you should do the reality
is most of your relationship plays out
behind closed doors you have to feel
like a really good version of yourself
with the person so stop focusing on who
the other person is on paper and start
looking at who you are with the person
date someone you would be with if nobody
else was looking
